The paper deals with graph theory and optimization, specifically the problem of finding cycle covers in graphs. This falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the usefulness of low congestion cycle covers in different settings of resilient computation, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NE). The paper also involves the study of graph algorithms and complexity, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Theoretical Computer Science (cs.GT).
